{
  "_about": "Ground-truth labels for the vlm_05 reference-diff anomaly benchmark. Each case pairs an inspection image with the clean reference it is diffed against. has_anomaly = frame-level label (primary binary metric). instances = OBJECT-level ground truth: one entry per real anomaly, with its type and an approximate bounding box in the REFERENCE image's pixel space (real ref = 1920x1080; variant ref = 1672x941; GPT frames are resized onto the real ref, so their boxes are also in 1920x1080). Boxes are intentionally generous; a detected instance = any kept region overlapping it. Types: object=forgotten object, graffiti, damage=vandalism/torn seat, litter=trash on floor. People are NOT instances (a kept box on a person is a false positive). source: real = frame from the actual camera, gpt = AI-inpainted test image on the real scene, variant = second synthetic scene with its own reference, self = a reference diffed against itself. The v2/v3/v4 negatives are CROSS-SESSION (different lighting vs the v1 reference) - the deployment-realistic negative case; known benign cross-session differences on this camera: onboard display content changes (bottom right), an equipment bag at the very bottom edge present in BOTH sessions, global exposure drift.",
